data.title: Anniversary dinner with my husband!
data.text:
We have been wanting to go to J. Coco for a long time so tonight was the night.
Made a reservation on Open Table and were seated right away.  The service was attentive but not overly so and the food was fabulous.  My husband had the Salmon Remoulade and I had the Braised short ribs - both were outstanding.

Be advised the noise level is high - but a definite winner in our book.

data.title: Date night awesomeness
data.text: Omg. So much great food.  Yum yum yum. Amazing place awesome staff.  Good food.  Bone marrow butter need i say more

data.title: One of our favorites
data.text: This is always a great experience for us.  Amazing food, great cocktails, nice wine selection, friendly staff.  The sea bass is a must, and the calamari is unique (not typical breaded and fried) the addition of salsa and avocado are great.  Daily specials are always enjoyable.

data.title: Great Food... Even better Customer Service
data.text: We ordered a Cubano, Cobb Salad, side of Mac and Cheese and a cup of soup. I asked for no mustard on the Cuban but when it came out it had mustard on it. My wife's Mac and Cheese also didn't come out with her food. They fixed the Cuban and quickly brought out the Mac and Cheese and we were content. To our surprise, the server (I think Hannah was her name) brought the bill at the end of the meal and comped both the Cuban and Mac and Cheese. We told her she didn't have to do that but she insisted. The place knows a thing about customer service and they won us over. We will definitely recommend this place to others and we will be back. Not to mention, the food was amazing and very well prepared.

data.title: Fun and so Good
data.text: We sat on the patio for dinner and loved it, it was cozy and the food was delicious! It started to get a bit cold so we headed inside and sat at the bar. We had so much fun talking with the different servers and the owner Jenny who is incredibly friendly!

data.title: What a wonderful little gem
data.text: We went to j. Coco on a recommendation from a friend-she did not disappoint nor did this restaurant. We called for a reservation-upon entering this beautiful little place we were immediately seated and was brought water. Our waitress came to our table to take our drink order and to let us know the specials-they all sounded wonderful. My husband had the Reuben with the Mac and cheese -it was so divine-I wish I had ordered it. I had the chicken curry soup that was also excellent!!!  We had a wonderful diner out-will come again

data.title: Great Food, but way Too Noisy.
data.text: Ate here while visiting our son and daughter-in-law.  The portions are huge.  Everyone loved their entrée.  We were seated promptly (I recommend a reservation) in an uncomfortable booth.  Son is 6'5" and had no leg room and complained about the back.  Our server was friendly and came back often to check on us.  I think any item on the menu would be a good choice, and can't recommend one over another.  The cocktails are interesting and quite tasty.  There is an adequate wine list as well.  The major issue here is the noise level.  By the time we finished eating we could not talk to one another and actually had to shout at the server.  Nevertheless,  I would definitely eat here again the next time we visit Omaha.

data.title: Swanky and cool
data.text: I stopped here for happy hour with a friend, we had two different cocktails and both were really good and we had the tater tots, they are highly recommended. The bartender was really nice, she was really quick, knew a lot about the cocktails and recommended the tater tots. I can't comment on the food other than the happy hour appetizer but I really enjoyed my visit and will return again soon.

data.title: Wonderful dinner
data.text: Love this restaurant! Great menu! Love the pork taco appetizers and had a fabulous wedge salad! Main dish was sea bass and had lots of crunchy veggies and was in a miso sauce. Loved it! Small, intimate and noisy! Its known for being noisy so we were expecting it ! Loved the peach cobbler for desert!

data.title: Elegantly Cool
data.text: Beautiful environment and lovely, delicious food. It is a real treat to dine at a fine dining restaurant with a nod to modernity.

data.title: Fine Food, Mid-Level Ambiance
data.text: Had a Thursday evening meal for two at the restaurant. Chose familiar Cobb salad and an order of bolognese with a glass of white wine. Bill with tip and tax was $55. The food was tasty. The service was adequate. The space for two was tight, seated close to others on a row of tables facing a wall booth. Our conversation was overridden by louder neighbors seated too close by. There were several open tables that evening with decent views out the front window. Stared into a wall the whole meal. Won't be back for a while.

data.title: Exquisite food
data.text: Love this place. A little pricey but worth it. Service excellent, especially Meghan. Food is just a great combination of flavors. In my opinion, stands alone in Omaha.

data.title: What a Great Place for dinner with friends.
data.text: Dinner for 4 couples. New and old friends. Very attentive service. Good wine list. Great offerings, especially the specials. I had the Chilean sea bass with vegetable pot stickers- very tasty! Appetizers included a platter of sautéed calamari and a flatbread dish. Also very good.

data.title: My first disappointment at J. Coco
data.text: Food, wine and atmosphere are the keys to this place's specialness for me. And that's why we went there on our anniversary. But service has consistently been only "okay". But last week was not a "totally satisfying customer service experience" (as we say in my job). I had to seek out the manager -- the server was seldom around - to get a new glass of ice that had a dead nat floating in it. Martini delivered with no garnish (that's also on the bartender -- and why does it always take about 5-10 minutes after I order until I get the beverage from the bar?). Had to ask twice for a wine glass for me, just brought one for my wife to go with our bottle of wine (cuz I had a martini?), and had to ask if they had any specials when she wanted to take our order. Just a lack of attention to details on the service side. Oh, the sea bass special was the best sea bass I can ever remember having.

data.title: Great Food, Great Wine
data.text: We have been here several times and always have had a delicious meal with wonderful service. Really like the ambience, a bit noisy but not so that it impedes conversation.

data.title: Exquisite food.
data.text: Interestingly unique food!  Leg of lamb was very tasty and presented with flair, Crispy schnitzel very tender and tasty. Salads nice and fresh with no preservatives on lettuce.  Very generous portions. While the noise level quite high our conversation was at it's limit.  We were by the door which made worse.  Overall, comfortable surroundings with efficient service.

data.title: Great lunch spot
data.text: Wonderful atmosphere, efficient service and terrific farm to table food. Had a wonderful salmon salad and a fabulous chicken entree. Dinner is even better- nightly specials are creative and thoughtfully prepared

data.title: Food good, service bad
data.text: I try and try to like this restaurant because one person I dine with when I visit Omaha loves the duck dish.  The food that we have ordered has been good.  The problem: every single time, the staff at this restaurant behaves as though we--and other patrons around us--are inconveniences to their evening. If this were Paris, I'd probably accept it, maybe even in New York City. Do not make the mistake of asking how a dish is prepared as it will be greeted with scorn. Do they not know the menu? Or do they have the expectation that if the chef cooks it, you'll eat it? The location is in a neighborhood in midtown Omaha, so if you live nearby, this restaurant is really the only option.  On the other hand, if you have a car, there are so many other restaurants in Omaha from which to choose for food that are just as delicious and innovative. If you are a person who tries to frequent locally owned establishments, Brushis, for example, off of 132nd and Dodge is an amazing restaurant. Every time we visit Omaha, we have also visited Brushis. In comparison, the food is delicious, ambience pleasant, and service welcoming and prompt.

data.title: Bucket List must!
data.text: The food by award winning Chef Jenny CoCo is truly a must for your Bucket List. The atmosphere and service is very impressive. Top notch wine list. Loved the presentation. Fine dining at its best. Save room for pastries!

data.title: Love it!
data.text:
Great Atmosphere
Great Drinks
Great Appetizers
Great Dinner 
Great Desserts
Good Service
Good Times!

I like how this is a trendy place where the 'up and coming' of Omaha go at the end of a long week.
